  (400,  'What type of animal is a dolphin?',                                                     'A mammal'),
  (400,  'What percentage of Earth''s surface is covered by water?',                              'Approximately 71%'),
  (400,  'What is the study of living organisms called?',                                         'Biology'),
  (400,  'What is the layer of Earth between the crust and the core called?',                    'The mantle'),
  (600,  'What is the name of the deepest known point in the ocean?',                            'Challenger Deep (in the Mariana Trench)'),
  (600,  'What is the term for an animal that is active during twilight hours — dawn and dusk?', 'Crepuscular'),
  (600,  'What warm ocean current keeps Western Europe milder than similar latitudes?',           'The Gulf Stream (North Atlantic Current)'),
  (600,  'What is the difference between a stalactite and a stalagmite?',                        'Stalactites hang from the ceiling; stalagmites grow from the floor'),
  (600,  'What is a constellation?',                                                              'A group of stars forming a recognisable pattern, traditionally named after figures, animals, or objects'),
  (600,  'What is the term for an organism that breaks down dead organic matter?',               'A decomposer (or detritivore)'),
  (600,  'What is the name of the process by which water moves through a plant from roots to leaves?', 'Transpiration'),
  (600,  'What is the outer solid layer of Earth called?',                                        'The lithosphere (comprising the crust and upper mantle)'),
  (800,  'What is the scientific term for the process by which trees shed their leaves in autumn?', 'Abscission'),
  (800,  'What is a territory in animal behaviour?',                                              'A geographic area an animal defends against others, especially of its own species'),
  (800,  'What is El Niño?',                                                                      'A weather phenomenon where central and eastern Pacific Ocean temperatures become unusually warm'),
  (800,  'What type of rock forms from compressed layers of sediment over long periods?',        'Sedimentary rock'),
  (800,  'What is thermohaline circulation?',                                                     'Large-scale ocean circulation driven by temperature and salinity differences (the ocean conveyor belt)'),
  (800,  'What is the symbiotic relationship between a clownfish and a sea anemone classified as?', 'Mutualism — both species benefit'),
  (800,  'What is a keystone species?',                                                           'A species with a disproportionately large effect on its ecosystem relative to its abundance'),
  (800,  'How many neurons does the human brain contain approximately?',                          'About 86 billion neurons'),
  (1000, 'What is the Coriolis effect in weather systems?',                                       'The deflection of winds and ocean currents caused by Earth''s rotation — rightward in the Northern Hemisphere'),
  (1000, 'What is upwelling in oceanography?',                                                   'The phenomenon where cold, nutrient-rich water rises to the ocean surface'),
  (1000, 'What is the aphotic zone of the ocean?',                                               'The zone where sunlight does not penetrate (also called the midnight or bathypelagic zone)'),
  (1000, 'What is nitrogen fixation?',                                                            'Bacteria converting atmospheric nitrogen gas (N₂) into ammonia (NH₃) that plants can use'),
  (1000, 'What is homeostasis?',                                                                  'The biological process by which living organisms maintain stable internal conditions despite external changes'),
  (1000, 'What is natal philopatry?',                                                             'The tendency of animals to return to their exact birthplace to reproduce'),
  (1000, 'What three periods make up the Mesozoic Era?',                                          'Triassic, Jurassic, and Cretaceous'),
  (1000, 'What geological epoch do we currently live in?',                                        'The Holocene epoch (some argue we have entered the Anthropocene)'),
